The paper deals with the problem of verbalizing OWL axioms of domain ontologies, which is a topic related to natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of semantic reduction at the logical level, which involves techniques from machine learning (ML) and computational linguistics (CL), making cs.LG and cs.IR likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper focuses on generating descriptions of individuals of SHIQ-based ontologies, which is a topic related to databases (DB), making cs.DB a possible sub-category.
